  <section id="Section520011">
    <title><anchor id="Anchor552222" role="Index"
    xreflabel="quantity on hand:by item group;item groups:quantity on hand for" />
    <indexterm significance="normal" zone="Anchor552222">
        <primary>quantity on hand</primary>

        <secondary>by item group</secondary>
      </indexterm> <indexterm significance="normal" zone="Anchor552222">
        <primary>item groups</primary>

        <secondary>quantity on hand for</secondary>
      </indexterm>Quantities on Hand by Item</title>

    <para id="Para520012">To view Quantities on Hand by Item, select the
    "Quantities on Hand by Item" option. The following screen will
    appear:</para>

    <para id="Para520016"><screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/IM_Disp_QOHByItem.png"
                       id="Graphic526626" />
          </imageobject>

          <caption id="Caption520017">Quantities on Hand by Item</caption>
        </mediaobject>
      </screenshot></para>

    <para id="Para520023">When displaying Quantities on Hand by Item, you are
    presented with the following options:</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para520024">Item Number</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x193a75c">
          <para>Enter the Item Number of the Item whose Quantity on Hand you
          want to display.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para672057">UOM</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x193a7a4">
          <para>Inventory Unit of Measure.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry role="openmfg">
        <term id="Para520028">All Warehouses</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x193a7c8">
          <para>Select to display Quantities on Hand by Item for all
          Warehouses.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry role="openmfg">
        <term id="Para520030">Selected</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x193a7ec">
          <para>Specify Warehouse whose Quantities on Hand by Item you want to
          display.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para572296">Show Inventory Value</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1940a24">
          <para>Select to include the Inventory value of Quantities on Hand by
          Item in the display.</para>

          <para id="Para572297">Specify whether to display Inventory value
          using Standard Costs or Actual Costs.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para520034">Use Standard Costs</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1940a6c">
          <para>Select to show Inventory value based on Standard Costs.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para520035">Use Actual Costs</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1940ab4">
          <para>Select to show Inventory value based on Actual Costs.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para520036">Quantities on Hand</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1940afc">
          <para>Display lists Quantities on Hand by Item, using the specified
          parameters.</para>

          <para id="Para675957">If the "Show Inventory Value" box is selected,
          the display will also show unit Cost, value, and non- netable value.
          Totals for each column will be calculated at the bottom of the
          display. If a Quantity on Hand value displays in the color orange,
          this means the actual or projected Quantity on Hand is at or below
          the Reorder Level. If the color is red, the current or projected
          Quantity on Hand is below 0.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

    <para id="Para520038">To the far right of the screen, the following
    buttons are available:</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para520039">CLOSE</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1940b68">
          <para>Closes the screen, returning you to the application
          desktop.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para610581">QUERY</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1940bb0">
          <para>Select to generate the display, using the specified
          parameters.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para675657">PRINT</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1940bf8">
          <para>Runs the report associated with this screen.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

    <para id="Para656119">Right-clicking on an Item in the Quantities on Hand
    list enables you to select from the following menu options:</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para656120">Transfer to another Warehouse</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1940c64">
          <para></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para656121">Adjust this QOH</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1940cac">
          <para></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para520044">Reset this QOH to 0</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1940cf4">
          <para></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para520045">Enter Misc. Count</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1940d3c">
          <para></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para520046">Issue Count Tag</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1940d84">
          <para></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <xi:include href="../widgets/xtreewidget.xml"
                  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                  xpointer="element(xtreewidget.menu.exportcontents)" />
    </variablelist>

